 &lt;li&gt; &lt;i&gt;Lightning:&lt;/i&gt; Once per day, when the wielder desires, a short spark of electricity can leap forth when the rod strikes an opponent to deal the normal damage for a &lt;i&gt;+2 light mace&lt;/i&gt; (1d6+2) and an extra 2d6 points of electricity damage. Even when the rod might not score a normal hit in combat, if the roll was good enough to count as a successful melee touch attack hit, then the 2d6 points of electricity damage still applies. The wielder activates this power as a free action, and it works if he strikes an opponent within 1 round.&lt;/li&gt;
