 &lt;li&gt; &lt;i&gt;Thunder and Lightning:&lt;/i&gt; Once per week as a standard action, the wielder of the rod can combine the &lt;i&gt;thunderclap&lt;/i&gt; described above with a lightning bolt, as in the &lt;i&gt;lightning stroke&lt;/i&gt;. The thunderclap affects all within 10 feet of the bolt. The &lt;i&gt;lightning stroke&lt;/i&gt; deals 9d6 points of electricity damage (count rolls of 1 or 2 as rolls of 3, for a range of 27 to 54 points), and the &lt;i&gt;thunderclap&lt;/i&gt; deals 2d6 points of sonic damage. A single DC 16 Reflex save applies for both effects.&lt;/li&gt;
