  (246, 'Shock', 'Weapon', 'Null', 'Yes', 'Moderate evocation', '8', '+1 bonus', 'Null', 'Craft Magic Arms and Armor, call lightning or lightning bolt', 'Null', 'Null', '&lt;div topic=&quot;Shock&quot; level=&quot;8&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Shock:&lt;/b&gt; Upon command, a shock weapon is sheathed in crackling electricity. The electricity does not harm the wielder. The effect remains until another command is given. A shock weapon deals an extra 1d6 points of electricity damage on a successful hit. Bows, crossbows, and slings so crafted bestow the electricity energy upon their ammunition.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Moderate evocation; CL 8th; Craft Magic Arms and Armor, &lt;i&gt;call lightning&lt;/i&gt; or &lt;i&gt;lightning bolt&lt;/i&gt;; Price +1 bonus.&lt;/p&gt;
